# modern swift: what's new since swift 5.3 (2020)

# context: the Big Nerd Ranch Guide (3rd ed, 2020) teaches swift 5 / 5.3.
# the fundamentals it covers are still 100% valid in 2026 — optionals,
# value vs reference types, structs/classes/enums, protocols, generics,
# closures, error handling, pattern matching, value semantics.
# everything below is ADDITIVE — language features that landed after the book.
# work through these after finishing the book, concurrency FIRST.


# 1. concurrency (swift 5.5, 2021) — THE big gap
# - async / await replaces completion-handler callbacks
# - structured concurrency: Task, TaskGroup, async let
# - actors + @MainActor for isolating shared mutable state
# - Sendable, AsyncSequence
# - modern swift is unrecognizable here vs 2020. don't skip.

# 2. swift 6 language mode / strict data-race safety (swift 6.0, 2024)
# - compile-time data-race checking, default for new projects
# - the thing that frustrates everyone: Sendable errors, actor isolation
# - tightly tied to #1; learn them together

# 3. macros + observation (swift 5.9, 2023)
# - macros: compile-time code generation (@attached / #freestanding)
# - @Observable replaces ObservableObject / @Published for state

# 4. quality-of-life syntax you'll see everywhere
# - if let foo { ... }        shorthand, no "= foo"  (5.7)
# - if / switch as expressions that return a value    (5.9)
# - first-class Regex type + regex literals           (5.7)
# - typed throws: throws(MyError)                      (6.0)
# - explicit any / some existential keywords

# 5. adjacent: SwiftUI
# - out of scope for the language book, but real-world UI is SwiftUI-first
# - leans heavily on #1 (concurrency) and #3 (@Observable)


# best free / current resources to fill the gaps
# - The Swift Programming Language book (free, swift.org) — kept current,
#   includes the concurrency chapters
# - Apple WWDC sessions: async/await, actors, "migrating to Swift 6"


# rough version timeline for reference
# 5.5  (2021)  async/await, actors, structured concurrency
# 5.6  (2022)  existential any, type placeholders
# 5.7  (2022)  if let shorthand, regex, Clock/Duration, some/any cleanup
# 5.9  (2023)  macros, if/switch expressions, parameter packs, @Observable
# 5.10 (2024)  full data isolation checking
# 6.0  (2024)  swift 6 mode (strict concurrency), typed throws, embedded swift
